name: Belinda Nesmith
text:
Well went to pick up the free food box at the Hanceville Civic Center this morning at 9:40 am. Not anyone there to give out! I arrived at 9:40 am
There were 3 vehicles already there waiting as well. But by 20:15 an still nobody there to give out boxes. We called the Mayor on speaker phone. He said they had given the boxes of food out earlier that morning. Well that was a waste of time. I was nearly late getting to dialysis treatment this morning. Grrr
At least they could of left a  note saying that all boxes had been given away. That way there would of not been a crowd there waiting till 10:30 am

name: Sarah Hodge
text: The building is nice, but the seats are horrible! Went to see the Nutcracker, the show was awesome, but was very uncomfortable in the kid seats they offer..two hours squeezed in with the little bitty arm stuck in my hip, I was on front row, so I finally moved to the bottom step of the floor to sit, found the hard floor to be more comfortable...BTW, the concession stand needs to clarify on there credit card only sign that it is a $5.00 minimum..but that was a minor issue compared to those horrible seats!

text: We found this place at the last minute for a graduation celebration. I thought everything was great until it was time to get back my deposit. When I inquired with Dot Crim about my "cash only" deposit she said that we broke a table. When I showed her the message from the parents that took out the tables out stating that the table was already broken I got nothing from her. BEWARE!
